  "text": "We previously reported selective expansion of TCRBV2 and TCRBV6S5 after in vitro stimulation of T-cells with recombinant streptococcal pyrogenic exotoxin-C (SPE-C) [CITATION_1] . We also reported polyclonal expansion of TCRBV2 and TCRBV6S5-bearing T-cells in patients in the acute phase of KD but not in those in the convalescent phase of KD or in age-matched controls [CITATION_2] . Furthermore, serum levels of anti-SPEC antibodies were significantly higher in patients with acute and convalescent KD than in age-matched controls, suggesting that these patients were infected with SPE-Cproducing streptococcus [CITATION_3] . These findings suggest a possible role of SPE-C in the pathogenesis of KD.",
